  "response": "Many movies have earned critical acclaim and popular adoration over the years. While tastes can be subjective, here are some films that are often regarded as must-watch:\n\n### Classic Films\n1. **Citizen Kane (1941)** - Directed by Orson Welles.\n2. **Casablanca (1942)** - Directed by Michael Curtiz.\n3. **Gone with the Wind (1939)** - Directed by Victor Fleming.\n4. **The Godfather (1972)** - Directed by Francis Ford Coppola.\n5. **Lawrence of Arabia (1962)** - Directed by David Lean.\n\n### Modern Classics\n1. **Pulp Fiction (1994)** - Directed by Quentin Tarantino.\n2. **Schindler's List (1993)** - Directed by Steven Spielberg.\n3. **Fight Club (1999)** - Directed by David Fincher.\n4. **The Shawshank Redemption (1994)** - Directed by Frank Darabont.\n5. **The Dark Knight (2008)** - Directed by Christopher Nolan.\n\n### Recent Acclaimed Films\n1. **Parasite (2019)** - Directed by Bong Joon-ho.\n2. **Mad Max: Fury Road (2015)** - Directed by George Miller.\n3. **La La Land (2016)** - Directed by Damien Chazelle.\n4. **Moonlight (2016)** - Directed by Barry Jenkins.\n5. **Get Out (2017)** - Directed by Jordan Peele.\n\n### Animation\n1. **Toy Story (1995)** - Directed by John Lasseter.\n2. **Spirited Away (2001)** - Directed by Hayao Miyazaki.\n3. **Up (2009)** - Directed by Pete Docter.\n4. **Coco (2017)** - Directed by Lee Unkrich and Adrian Molina.\n5. **Inside Out (2015)** - Directed by Pete Docter.\n\n### Foreign Films\n1. **Am\u00e9lie (2001)** - Directed by Jean-Pierre Jeunet.\n2. **Life is Beautiful (1997)** - Directed by Roberto Benigni.\n3. **Pan's Labyrinth (2006)** - Directed by Guillermo del Toro.\n4. **City of God (2002)** - Directed by Fernando Meirelles and K\u00e1tia Lund.\n5. **The Lives of Others (2006)** - Directed by Florian Henckel von Donnersmarck.\n\nThese films span various genres and eras, offering a diverse array of storytelling, cinematography, and emotion. Keep in mind that the \"best\" movies can vary greatly depending on personal preference and cultural context.",
